1
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:19,427
The medicine bottle.

2
00:00:22,773 --> 00:00:25,075
I'm trying to catch the medicine bottle.

3
00:00:29,217 --> 00:00:31,060
But I couldn't grab it.

4
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:34,960
I grabbed it.

5
00:00:40,589 --> 00:00:42,349
It's okay.

6
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:47,222
You did your best to save the grandpa.

7
00:00:50,808 --> 00:00:52,943
I couldn't help.

8
00:00:56,831 --> 00:00:59,167
You're right.

9
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:01,302
It's not your fault.

10
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:13,789
You don't need
to feel guilty or afraid anymore.

11
00:01:26,584 --> 00:01:28,510
In a little bit

12
00:01:29,825 --> 00:01:32,210
when the alarm goes off,

13
00:01:33,132 --> 00:01:35,100
open your eyes.

14
00:01:38,564 --> 00:01:40,950
When you open your eyes...

15
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,903
you can...

16
00:01:48,434 --> 00:01:51,153
get on a plane.

17
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,896
You can get on a plane...

18
00:02:00,034 --> 00:02:05,381
and you can go anywhere.

19
00:02:49,751 --> 00:02:53,542
When you open your eyes,

20
00:02:53,542 --> 00:02:56,250
you can get on a plane.

21
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,334
You can get on a plane...

22
00:02:58,334 --> 00:03:01,308
and you can go anywhere.

23
00:03:03,529 --> 00:03:08,501
Nae Il keeps saying
more weird stuff these days.

24
00:03:11,618 --> 00:03:13,837
When did she leave, by the way?

25
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:03,584
Didn't you hurt your hand?

26
00:04:04,918 --> 00:04:06,500
I lied.

27
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,380
Why?

28
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:11,292
I wanted you to be the soloist.

29
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:14,834
If it was a fair process,
of course you'd have been voted.

30
00:04:14,834 --> 00:04:16,343
But...

31
00:04:17,792 --> 00:04:19,709
I'm sorry, Shi Won.

32
00:04:19,709 --> 00:04:21,220
I can't give up.

33
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,893
I know that I'm not as good as you,

34
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:28,360
but I want to do this.

35
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:31,000
I'll work hard.

36
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,626
As for how much I care about the orchestra,

37
00:04:33,626 --> 00:04:37,306
I don't want to fall

38
00:04:38,221 --> 00:04:40,064
behind you or Yoo Jin.

39
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:49,331
Idiot! I made it clear to you.

40
00:04:49,334 --> 00:04:51,430
You're more than qualified to be a soloist.

41
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:54,428
What did you take me for?

42
00:05:03,465 --> 00:05:07,125
Still, thank you.

43
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:09,052
I'm touched.

44
00:05:26,410 --> 00:05:29,731
By the way,
what's happening to our orchestra?

45
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:46,355
Why did you do that?

46
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:49,709
[Rental Sign-In Sheet]

47
00:05:49,709 --> 00:05:52,250
One of our members

48
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,806
must have rented one?

49
00:05:56,918 --> 00:05:57,751
[Cha Yoo Jin]

50
00:05:57,751 --> 00:06:00,334
As for the Sae Hyun video clip,

51
00:06:00,334 --> 00:06:02,250
I can understand

52
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,167
that you wanted the members to be on alert
as a conductor.

53
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,181
But

54
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:09,203
why didn't you mention
the observation camera?

55
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:12,929
You said you wanted Rising Start to break up.

56
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:14,818
It's going as you wished.

57
00:06:14,818 --> 00:06:17,667
You said you'd stitch it up somehow.

58
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:19,751
So why are you doing this?

59
00:06:19,751 --> 00:06:20,751
What's wrong with you?

60
00:06:20,751 --> 00:06:24,341
Whatever your reason was,
you're the one who will get hurt the most.

61
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:27,542
Being nosy is contagious,

62
00:06:27,542 --> 00:06:29,382
probably because of Nae Il.

63
00:06:31,876 --> 00:06:33,169
Who knows.

64
00:06:34,042 --> 00:06:36,514
If I said it's because I trust them,

65
00:06:37,258 --> 00:06:39,143
am I being too reckless?

66
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,876
Almighty Cha, it's okay.

67
00:07:01,876 --> 00:07:03,950
Just do what we did at the rehearsal.

68
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,460
It's okay, Cha Yoo Jin!

69
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:36,334
The rest of the members didn't come?

70
00:07:36,334 --> 00:07:38,250
They got dragged out and called away.

71
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,787
All their family members want us to quit.

72
00:07:41,889 --> 00:07:44,417
I heard
that the board will determine tomorrow

73
00:07:44,417 --> 00:07:46,876
if they should cancel our performance.

74
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:52,082
- What do we do now?
- What do you mean what do we do?

75
00:07:52,082 --> 00:07:54,334
Have we been driving on the highway?

76
00:07:54,334 --> 00:07:56,094
We've always driven on unpaved roads.

77
00:07:57,394 --> 00:08:00,209
We all have our own battles.

78
00:08:00,209 --> 00:08:02,626
Let's try to convince everyone.

79
00:08:02,626 --> 00:08:04,185
- Yes!
- Okay!

80
00:08:07,425 --> 00:08:11,145
Why don't we just quit now?

81
00:08:18,434 --> 00:08:21,779
You've done as much as you could.

82
00:08:22,946 --> 00:08:24,080
Aren't you tired?

83
00:08:33,915 --> 00:08:36,083
Sunbae, just six hours.

84
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,042
You're not doing anything anyway.

85
00:08:38,042 --> 00:08:38,918
Just six hours.

86
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:42,125
Once things get resolved
and our performance is over.

87
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:43,883
The performance is next week.

88
00:08:43,883 --> 00:08:46,125
It's a request by "my Nae Il".
Can't you help me?

89
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:48,042
- It's a request by 'My Nae Il.'
- That 'My Nae Il'...

90
00:08:48,042 --> 00:08:51,334
I told you not to say that!
When did I say "my..."?

91
00:08:51,334 --> 00:08:53,125
Should I summon my witnesses?

92
00:08:53,125 --> 00:08:55,979
Lak, Mini Min Hee, Mr. Curly Hair,
where are you?

93
00:08:55,979 --> 00:08:59,240
Where is everyone?

94
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:03,375
♪ Promise me ♪

95
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:08,040
If you hang out with me for just six hours,
"my Nae Il" will forever...

96
00:09:09,529 --> 00:09:10,918
Got it.

97
00:09:10,918 --> 00:09:12,712
Only for six hours.

98
00:09:13,703 --> 00:09:15,755
So, what are you going to do?

99
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:24,364
Let's just break up!

100
00:09:32,295 --> 00:09:36,186
That actor looks exactly like you.

101
00:09:36,186 --> 00:09:38,446
That's ridiculous.

102
00:09:39,496 --> 00:09:42,083
Look at him. He's hopeless.

103
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:45,584
Don't wear sweatpants outside!

104
00:09:45,584 --> 00:09:47,864
Are you twins, by any chance?

105
00:09:47,864 --> 00:09:48,918
You want to pick a fight?

106
00:09:48,918 --> 00:09:51,334
I'm not picking on a fight.

107
00:09:51,334 --> 00:09:52,834
Just one bite.

108
00:09:52,834 --> 00:09:54,250
I'm not eating. I'm full!

109
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,834
Just one bite!

110
00:09:55,834 --> 00:09:57,334
I'm not going to eat it.

111
00:09:57,334 --> 00:09:59,375
Just one bite!

112
00:09:59,375 --> 00:10:01,093
Quiet please!

113
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:20,670
Where are you going?

114
00:10:39,515 --> 00:10:43,068
I'm not. I'm different from you.

115
00:10:44,186 --> 00:10:46,446
Jesus Christ.

116
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,949
I'm losing my mind.

117
00:10:59,076 --> 00:11:00,669
Success!

118
00:11:05,728 --> 00:11:07,112
Yes!

119
00:11:08,377 --> 00:11:10,971
Hey, I told you I'd do it.

120
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:20,209
Do you want anything?

121
00:11:20,209 --> 00:11:21,924
Just tell me.

122
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:23,942
Don't smile.

123
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:26,876
Let's go get coffee.

124
00:11:26,876 --> 00:11:29,292
Wait. Wear the scarf.

125
00:11:29,292 --> 00:11:30,375
Why?

126
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:31,834
It's too cold out.

127
00:11:31,834 --> 00:11:33,375
I don't want to! Hey!

128
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:35,730
Wait, just listen to me.

129
00:12:16,445 --> 00:12:17,996
Hey, time's up.

130
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:21,291
It's over, Seol Nae Il.

131
00:12:22,325 --> 00:12:26,079
Yes. It's over, Sunbae.

132
00:12:26,914 --> 00:12:28,716
It's so hot.

133
00:12:48,519 --> 00:12:49,861
Sunbae.

134
00:12:52,189 --> 00:12:56,076
Everyone will show up for practice tomorrow.

135
00:12:56,777 --> 00:13:00,706
S members said
they'd convince everyone today.

136
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:04,459
Yeah, I know.

137
00:13:05,536 --> 00:13:09,923
The board won't say much either.

138
00:13:10,683 --> 00:13:14,069
A members said they'd convince them.

139
00:13:15,195 --> 00:13:17,375
I know. I'm going in.

140
00:13:17,375 --> 00:13:18,499
What?

141
00:13:19,216 --> 00:13:20,233
Huh?

142
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,087
I meant, go on in.

143
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:37,351
I had fun on our date today, Sunbae.

144
00:13:44,116 --> 00:13:47,169
Did she become pretty
or did something happen to me?

145
00:13:51,623 --> 00:13:53,800
Why do I feel this way about Nae Il,
out of nowhere?

146
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:08,708
I guess you were reckless, Cha Yoo Jin.

147
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:12,539
You didn't expect this to happen?

148
00:15:13,539 --> 00:15:15,966
Did you think that the members would hold on?

149
00:15:18,861 --> 00:15:20,412
I guess.

150
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:23,807
I didn't think this would happen.

151
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:27,669
It's discouraging.

152
00:15:28,746 --> 00:15:30,756
And a little unexpected.

153
00:15:36,061 --> 00:15:38,280
It's no fun having an honest Cha Yoo Jin.

154
00:15:41,046 --> 00:15:43,014
What are you going to do now?

155
00:15:45,073 --> 00:15:48,417
It looks like
you are following me around more these days.

156
00:15:48,417 --> 00:15:50,109
Just answer me.

157
00:15:51,018 --> 00:15:52,945
I don't know
since I haven't thought about it.

158
00:15:54,105 --> 00:15:58,200
I'll have to start from the beginning.

159
00:15:59,262 --> 00:16:02,113
We don't know
how the board will decide, right?

160
00:16:02,113 --> 00:16:04,866
I can make a guess.

161
00:16:04,866 --> 00:16:08,792
Cancel the approval, close the practice room.

162
00:16:08,792 --> 00:16:11,046
If that's the worst possible outcome,

163
00:16:12,597 --> 00:16:15,751
we can still perform without any approval.

164
00:16:15,751 --> 00:16:20,055
If the practice room is closed,
should we practice in the lobby?

165
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:29,190
That's interesting, a concert in the lobby.

166
00:16:32,445 --> 00:16:36,198
You're no fun like this.

167
00:16:39,685 --> 00:16:44,209
I didn't understand
why everyone I liked, liked you...

168
00:16:44,209 --> 00:16:46,081
You talk too much.

169
00:16:46,715 --> 00:16:48,225
Let me think a little.

170
00:16:50,161 --> 00:16:51,837
Go to the professors' meeting room.

171
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:57,584
Everyone's over there.

172
00:16:57,584 --> 00:16:58,928
What?

173
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:01,363
Here they come.

174
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:39,876
Yeon Seok, why is he here
when he said he'd go for lessons?

175
00:17:39,876 --> 00:17:42,667
My nephew is there, too.

176
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:46,000
He's usually good,
so what is wrong with him all of a sudden?

177
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:51,500
They're protesting to show us on a cold day.

178
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:55,042
They've been hanging out with S or whatever,
the incompetent ones.

179
00:17:55,042 --> 00:17:56,185
Did they learn from them?

180
00:17:56,185 --> 00:17:59,105
They used to only know about themselves,

181
00:17:59,105 --> 00:18:01,240
but they're getting along with others now.

182
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:07,375
Most of them will be alone again
once they graduate.

183
00:18:07,375 --> 00:18:10,167
I like what I see now.

184
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:15,129
Getting along like that,
they can do it only at that age.

185
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:21,876
She's even wearing a skirt..

186
00:18:21,876 --> 00:18:24,930
I can see her efforts.

187
00:18:57,219 --> 00:19:02,392
Dozens of sounds come together
to create one sound in an orchestra.

188
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:09,125
No, dozens of people get together
and create a melody.

189
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:14,013
Violins, violas, contrabasses.

190
00:19:14,013 --> 00:19:18,375
When the trumpets do their own part
in their position

191
00:19:18,375 --> 00:19:21,375
Mozart becomes Mozart

192
00:19:21,375 --> 00:19:25,282
and Tchaikovsky sounds like Tchaikovsky.

193
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:31,876
Everyone has to maintain their position

194
00:19:31,876 --> 00:19:34,083
and come together to complete the music.

195
00:19:53,719 --> 00:19:57,231
Why don't we just quit now?

196
00:19:59,941 --> 00:20:03,119
You've done as much as you could.

197
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,869
Aren't you tired?

198
00:20:09,018 --> 00:20:11,153
Then what about our conductor?

199
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:15,083
That's not right.

200
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:18,661
Yoon Hoo, we have someone who trusts us.

201
00:20:18,661 --> 00:20:22,381
We can't let go of that hand
just because we're tired.

202
00:20:23,056 --> 00:20:24,816
That's not right.

203
00:20:26,317 --> 00:20:29,584
Okay, I'll start convincing them now.
Let's go!

204
00:20:29,584 --> 00:20:31,042
Let's go!

205
00:20:31,042 --> 00:20:32,983
Let's go!

206
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:17,077
Yes, I understand.

207
00:21:21,235 --> 00:21:25,038
How did the board decide?

208
00:21:29,206 --> 00:21:31,966
- Sunbae!
- Mini Min Hee!

209
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:51,694
This is great!

210
00:21:53,547 --> 00:21:55,542
- What are you doing?
- What are you doing?

211
00:21:55,542 --> 00:21:57,167
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

212
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:59,542
- We just need to perform well.
- Yes!

213
00:21:59,542 --> 00:22:02,417
Yes, we just need to perform well.
Sae Hyun will lose!

214
00:22:02,417 --> 00:22:03,947
That's right!

215
00:22:05,918 --> 00:22:07,789
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

216
00:22:09,918 --> 00:22:11,667
Yes!

217
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:12,667
What?

218
00:23:03,591 --> 00:23:07,334
Of course my Nae Il is the best!

219
00:23:07,334 --> 00:23:10,757
Maybe because it's your last day,
it sounded better.

220
00:23:11,307 --> 00:23:12,751
Did it?

221
00:23:12,751 --> 00:23:15,292
Anyway, I'll be so sad.

222
00:23:15,292 --> 00:23:17,931
You should've said yes
when the boss asked you to stay.

223
00:23:21,151 --> 00:23:23,078
- Mini Min Hee.
- Yes?

224
00:23:27,156 --> 00:23:28,866
A gift for you.

225
00:23:28,866 --> 00:23:31,626
You collected these.

226
00:23:31,626 --> 00:23:33,292
Coupons for Chinese food!

227
00:23:33,292 --> 00:23:37,367
Coupons for fried pork and even cafe coupons!

228
00:23:38,709 --> 00:23:41,584
Are you really giving these to me?

229
00:23:41,584 --> 00:23:43,876
Yes! Have them, Mini Min Hee.

230
00:23:43,876 --> 00:23:46,500
Wow, Nae Il, you have a big heart now.

231
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:48,500
Did you hit the lottery?

232
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:51,000
Give and take.

233
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:54,876
Take a big dip in the whip cream you like.

234
00:23:54,876 --> 00:23:56,386
Thank you.

235
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:04,834
When I'm done working here,
I won't see you often anymore.

236
00:24:04,834 --> 00:24:07,000
I'm sad.

237
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,209
I won't get
to eat my favorite waffles anymore.

238
00:24:09,209 --> 00:24:12,069
Come often. I'll make it for you.

239
00:24:12,786 --> 00:24:16,923
And you should show yourself often
to your mother-in-law.

240
00:24:18,807 --> 00:24:20,859
Mini Min Hee.

241
00:24:23,614 --> 00:24:25,626
Take care of yourself.

242
00:24:25,626 --> 00:24:28,126
Of course, I take care of myself.

243
00:24:31,270 --> 00:24:34,865
Hey, aren't you going a little overboard
for quitting a part-time job?

244
00:24:37,059 --> 00:24:39,459
Hey, I can't breathe.

245
00:24:39,459 --> 00:24:40,806
Hey!

246
00:24:46,136 --> 00:24:47,813
Milch!

247
00:24:56,914 --> 00:24:59,174
Baby.

248
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,375
If you came here
to stop Yoo Jin's study abroad,

249
00:25:03,375 --> 00:25:05,389
you shouldn't.

250
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:08,834
I know.

251
00:25:08,834 --> 00:25:12,921
I came to ask you to go with Sunbae.

252
00:25:13,597 --> 00:25:15,815
Do you mean that?

253
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:21,209
Milch,

254
00:25:21,209 --> 00:25:24,042
even if Yoo Jin says he doesn't want to go,

255
00:25:24,042 --> 00:25:25,934
please take him with you.

256
00:25:27,138 --> 00:25:29,232
Because he can go now.

257
00:25:30,697 --> 00:25:35,209
Even if he gets stubborn,
you have to take him.

258
00:25:36,495 --> 00:25:38,713
I'll put my faith in you.

259
00:25:41,090 --> 00:25:42,553
Baby.

260
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:18,209
You're crying again.

261
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:20,280
I can't just let you go.

262
00:26:22,611 --> 00:26:24,705
I got something in my eye.

263
00:26:31,956 --> 00:26:34,334
I heard you were getting lessons from Milch.

264
00:26:34,334 --> 00:26:36,046
Is that why you came here?

265
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:37,946
Yes.

266
00:26:38,667 --> 00:26:41,563
It's a lesson
to make sure I don't bother Cha Yoo Jin.

267
00:26:44,683 --> 00:26:48,069
There is something
I have to tell you, Yoon Hoo Sunbae.

268
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:50,918
Why don't you do it next time?

269
00:26:50,918 --> 00:26:52,209
I don't want to hear it today.

270
00:26:52,209 --> 00:26:53,939
I have to tell you today.

271
00:26:55,138 --> 00:26:57,523
I shouldn't put it off any longer.

272
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:01,279
You're mean, Seol Nae Il.

273
00:27:04,343 --> 00:27:05,977
Yoon Hoo Sunbae.

274
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:11,132
Thank you for liking my piano performances.

275
00:27:12,674 --> 00:27:17,019
I was also really happy
when you asked me to play a duet with you.

276
00:27:20,807 --> 00:27:22,901
And...

277
00:27:25,687 --> 00:27:29,449
thank you so much for liking me.

278
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:36,481
I'm okay with hope torture.

279
00:27:38,575 --> 00:27:42,212
Don't define it, don't draw a line.

280
00:27:43,622 --> 00:27:45,424
You should've just left it.

281
00:27:46,290 --> 00:27:47,843
I can't do that.

282
00:27:48,669 --> 00:27:51,430
I'm an expert in having a crush,

283
00:27:53,674 --> 00:27:56,560
but it hurts too much.

284
00:27:59,413 --> 00:28:02,716
Yes, it hurts.

285
00:28:07,963 --> 00:28:13,135
So why do you look
like you're hurting more than I am?

286
00:28:17,614 --> 00:28:19,291
Are you really okay?

287
00:28:21,272 --> 00:28:23,542
Of course!

288
00:28:23,542 --> 00:28:25,589
You don't need to worry about me anymore.

289
00:28:32,616 --> 00:28:36,667
A conductor is a guide.

290
00:28:36,667 --> 00:28:39,959
I recommended you

291
00:28:39,959 --> 00:28:43,924
because I believe
that your personality fits the bill.

292
00:28:44,750 --> 00:28:46,959
But Cha Yoo Jin is your only pupil, right?

293
00:28:46,959 --> 00:28:49,796
Do you want to become my pupil?

294
00:28:49,796 --> 00:28:52,292
Then just like Cha Yoo Jin,
being an assistant and running errands...

295
00:28:52,292 --> 00:28:54,225
I heard about that.

296
00:28:55,206 --> 00:28:57,842
I don't want to do that.

297
00:29:02,066 --> 00:29:07,413
When you told me to become a conductor,
I was happy.

298
00:29:08,523 --> 00:29:13,209
I know how amazing it is to feel
when instruments come to life.

299
00:29:13,209 --> 00:29:14,488
I was confident, too.

300
00:29:14,488 --> 00:29:16,959
You were too confident.

301
00:29:16,959 --> 00:29:21,375
You were already tuning
the scores and intonation.

302
00:29:21,375 --> 00:29:25,131
You already had your own style,
so I guess that's natural.

303
00:29:25,766 --> 00:29:29,987
But there is one thing that worries me.

304
00:29:32,787 --> 00:29:39,260
You're arrogant
and you only accept people you deem talented.

305
00:29:40,834 --> 00:29:43,809
If someone can shatter your arrogance,

306
00:29:43,809 --> 00:29:47,153
he's your mentor, not me.

307
00:29:50,649 --> 00:29:53,777
Yes. The Salzburg Competition?

308
00:29:53,777 --> 00:29:54,417
Are you saying

309
00:29:54,417 --> 00:29:58,209
that Nae Il can audition
for the Salzburg Competition?

310
00:29:58,209 --> 00:30:00,917
But how?

311
00:30:01,906 --> 00:30:03,000
Does it mean

312
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,706
that Nae Il will enter
the international competition?

313
00:30:05,706 --> 00:30:09,751
Yes, it's a right given to the award winners
at the Baek Geon Soo Competition.

314
00:30:09,751 --> 00:30:12,546
And Nae Il was included.

315
00:30:12,546 --> 00:30:14,751
How did Nae Il make it?

316
00:30:14,751 --> 00:30:18,184
It looks like
Professor Yoon Yi Song sent a recommendation.

317
00:30:18,944 --> 00:30:22,789
That strict woman did such commendable work.

318
00:30:23,849 --> 00:30:25,907
Nae Il will be very happy.

319
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:28,500
I haven't talked to her yet.

320
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,363
Her cellphone is off.

321
00:30:32,497 --> 00:30:37,751
The cellphone is turned off,

322
00:30:37,751 --> 00:30:39,914
please leave a message...

323
00:30:46,070 --> 00:30:48,372
Nae Il! Seol Nae Il!

324
00:30:49,504 --> 00:30:51,847
Answer me if you're inside!

325
00:31:02,429 --> 00:31:05,125
Have you seen Nae Il today?

326
00:31:05,125 --> 00:31:07,542
Has anyone seen her
either in school or anywhere else?

327
00:31:07,542 --> 00:31:08,751
Nae Il?

328
00:31:08,751 --> 00:31:10,459
Now I think about it,
I haven't seen her all day.

329
00:31:10,459 --> 00:31:11,500
Why don't you call her?

330
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:13,792
Nae Il's cellphone has been off.

331
00:31:13,792 --> 00:31:16,334
I thought it was odd, so I kept calling her.

332
00:31:16,334 --> 00:31:18,083
What's odd?

333
00:31:18,083 --> 00:31:21,584
Nae Il gave me all her coupons.

334
00:31:21,584 --> 00:31:23,006
She did?

335
00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:26,834
She gave me
pictures of Almighty Cha yesterday.

336
00:31:26,834 --> 00:31:29,083
I thought it was strange.

337
00:31:29,083 --> 00:31:30,840
What's going on with Nae Il?

338
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:40,626
Hey, quiet!

339
00:31:40,626 --> 00:31:43,792
Nae Il sleeps in often with her phone off.

340
00:31:43,792 --> 00:31:45,814
I'm telling you that she's inside!

341
00:31:53,622 --> 00:31:55,632
Open the door, Nae Il!

342
00:31:58,043 --> 00:32:00,053
I'm coming in.

343
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:34,375
Min Hee, look everywhere
that Nae Il would go.

344
00:32:34,375 --> 00:32:36,292
Her phone is off.

345
00:32:36,292 --> 00:32:37,301
Yes.

346
00:32:38,250 --> 00:32:41,375
Look for her
in the lesson room, the cafe and everywhere.

347
00:32:41,375 --> 00:32:43,459
I'm not sure though.

348
00:32:43,459 --> 00:32:45,740
Nae Il quit her part-time job
at the kindergarten,

349
00:32:45,740 --> 00:32:48,334
so I can only think of home and school.

350
00:32:48,334 --> 00:32:50,417
I don't have anywhere else to look.

351
00:32:50,417 --> 00:32:52,964
I think she planned this and went somewhere.

352
00:32:53,974 --> 00:32:58,361
She couldn't have done
something horrible, could she?

353
00:32:59,462 --> 00:33:01,918
Hey, how can you say that?

354
00:33:01,918 --> 00:33:03,167
He's right!

355
00:33:03,167 --> 00:33:04,517
Nae Il!

356
00:33:06,026 --> 00:33:07,626
I didn't mean that.

357
00:33:07,626 --> 00:33:09,772
Sunbae, I'm hanging up.

358
00:33:36,391 --> 00:33:38,902
Please turn on the phone.

359
00:34:19,977 --> 00:34:22,863
My legs hurt so much,
I can't walk anymore.

360
00:34:23,522 --> 00:34:25,125
It's been over 24 hours,

361
00:34:25,125 --> 00:34:26,908
so they'll take
the missing person's report now, right?

362
00:34:28,735 --> 00:34:31,329
Let's go and request a report.

363
00:34:32,514 --> 00:34:36,484
What if something really happened to Nae Il?

364
00:34:43,918 --> 00:34:45,459
[Seol Nae Il]

365
00:34:46,376 --> 00:34:47,896
It's Nae Il!

366
00:34:48,755 --> 00:34:49,960
What?

367
00:34:52,249 --> 00:34:54,502
Hello? Nae Il!

368
00:34:55,526 --> 00:34:58,370
And? Where is Seol Nae Il now?

369
00:34:59,409 --> 00:35:01,294
She didn't get hurt?

370
00:35:03,187 --> 00:35:05,030
Jeju Island?

371
00:35:05,820 --> 00:35:07,914
She went home to Jeju Island?

372
00:35:25,165 --> 00:35:26,793
It looks great.

373
00:35:27,412 --> 00:35:29,714
You shouldn't do that, girl.

374
00:35:30,765 --> 00:35:33,700
What worry?
I didn't even know you disappeared.

375
00:35:33,700 --> 00:35:35,250
Keep talking.

376
00:35:35,250 --> 00:35:37,542
Yoo Jin is on his way here. He's nearby.

377
00:35:37,542 --> 00:35:40,584
I skipped my meals since yesterday
for someone like her!

378
00:35:40,584 --> 00:35:43,167
I guess Yoo Jin didn't worry about me either.

379
00:35:43,167 --> 00:35:45,834
I don't know. Why don't you call and ask him?

380
00:35:45,834 --> 00:35:46,792
I see.

381
00:35:46,792 --> 00:35:48,125
Wait!

382
00:35:48,125 --> 00:35:50,467
When are you coming back?

383
00:35:50,467 --> 00:35:54,500
The coupon you gave me,
the fried pork can't be delivered.

384
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:56,375
So you should come back quickly
and resolve this.

385
00:35:56,375 --> 00:35:58,042
It's not for delivery?

386
00:35:58,042 --> 00:36:01,027
That's right!
So I think you should come back soon.

387
00:36:01,881 --> 00:36:05,209
Don't hang up. You should come quickly.

388
00:36:05,209 --> 00:36:07,500
He's doing that again.

389
00:36:07,500 --> 00:36:10,453
Does he know
that I collected those from my friends?

390
00:36:12,155 --> 00:36:16,375
But Mini Min Hee,
I only got them from my friends.

391
00:36:16,375 --> 00:36:19,459
Why don't you tell him
that I didn't pick them up on the street?

392
00:36:19,459 --> 00:36:21,047
Seol Nae Il.

393
00:36:22,307 --> 00:36:24,567
What the hell are you doing?

394
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,250
Seol Nae Il.

395
00:36:33,250 --> 00:36:35,887
- Did she hang up?
- Did she hang up?

396
00:36:35,887 --> 00:36:38,876
You yelled at her,
that's why she got scared and hung up!

397
00:36:38,876 --> 00:36:40,500
You might hit her.

398
00:36:40,500 --> 00:36:43,061
Even for you, Almighty Cha, that's not right.

399
00:36:43,061 --> 00:36:44,709
I just raised my voice a little.

400
00:36:44,709 --> 00:36:48,042
Raise your voice, yell at her
and beat her up!

401
00:36:48,042 --> 00:36:51,828
She felt depressed and went home.
You shouldn't do that, Yoo Jin!

402
00:36:52,963 --> 00:36:55,307
I'm disappointed in you, Almighty Cha.

403
00:36:56,186 --> 00:36:57,876
Just give me back my cellphone.

404
00:36:57,876 --> 00:36:59,042
It's confiscated.

405
00:36:59,042 --> 00:37:00,336
What?

406
00:37:12,566 --> 00:37:15,243
I should've listen to his voice a little more
before hanging up.

407
00:37:33,168 --> 00:37:34,709
Really?

408
00:37:34,709 --> 00:37:36,914
You already have a break?

409
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:43,347
I did really well on my study,
so I got my break early this time.

410
00:37:44,721 --> 00:37:49,918
Then you'll receive a scholarship, too?

411
00:37:49,918 --> 00:37:54,000
Mom, there is no scholarship at our school.

412
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:57,310
Can't you tell by now
since I haven't received one yet?

413
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:04,959
Have this.

414
00:38:04,959 --> 00:38:07,542
I heard it's good for you,
so I brought it for you.

415
00:38:07,542 --> 00:38:09,906
What's this?

416
00:38:10,747 --> 00:38:16,834
My goodness, you should take this.
Why give it to me?

417
00:38:16,834 --> 00:38:20,333
It's nice to eat together,
thanks to her break.

418
00:38:21,910 --> 00:38:27,209
Hey, a new kindergarten opened up nearby.

419
00:38:27,209 --> 00:38:29,375
It's good for you.

420
00:38:29,375 --> 00:38:32,845
You can get a good job without going far.

421
00:38:35,897 --> 00:38:38,792
You know how your father got you
a big place in Seoul

422
00:38:38,792 --> 00:38:41,709
and now we're about to go broke.

423
00:38:41,709 --> 00:38:43,500
So you should get a job soon.

424
00:38:43,500 --> 00:38:47,068
And how can he sign a two-year contract?

425
00:38:48,370 --> 00:38:49,876
After the two years,

426
00:38:49,876 --> 00:38:52,716
get ready to move
to a smaller place right away.

427
00:38:53,873 --> 00:38:58,125
Okay. I can move next year.

428
00:38:58,125 --> 00:39:00,915
There won't be anyone next door anyway.

429
00:39:03,132 --> 00:39:06,292
Nae Il, why don't you play the piano for me?

430
00:39:06,292 --> 00:39:09,382
Let me hear that pretty sound.

431
00:39:10,324 --> 00:39:13,752
Grandma, next time.

432
00:39:14,393 --> 00:39:15,986
I'll play it next time.

433
00:39:17,983 --> 00:39:19,993
Please excuse me.

434
00:39:30,298 --> 00:39:33,684
She's always been weird.

435
00:39:42,714 --> 00:39:44,584
Cha Yoo Jin!

436
00:39:44,584 --> 00:39:46,002
Cha Yoo Jin.

437
00:39:49,713 --> 00:39:51,209
What? Do I look weird?

438
00:39:51,209 --> 00:39:52,792
Yes.

439
00:39:52,798 --> 00:39:54,002
To me too.

440
00:39:54,002 --> 00:39:55,751
By the way, where is Nae Il?

441
00:39:55,751 --> 00:39:57,584
Why can't I reach her?

442
00:39:57,584 --> 00:39:58,959
She went to Jeju Island.

443
00:39:58,959 --> 00:40:01,417
Jeju Island? When is she coming back?

444
00:40:01,417 --> 00:40:04,103
I'm not sure either. What is it about?

445
00:40:05,713 --> 00:40:07,348
It's a recommendation
for an international competition.

446
00:40:09,618 --> 00:40:12,212
If Seol Nae Il applies,
she can participate right away.

447
00:40:13,062 --> 00:40:15,982
If she wins first place,
she can study abroad with a full scholarship.

448
00:40:15,982 --> 00:40:17,908
Talk to her soon.

449
00:40:26,951 --> 00:40:29,253
I'm leaving a voicemail,
so listen to it whenever you want to.

450
00:40:30,389 --> 00:40:32,023
Seol Nae Il.

451
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:36,083
You can enter a competition.

452
00:40:36,083 --> 00:40:37,292
If you win,

453
00:40:37,292 --> 00:40:39,305
you can get a full ride
for your study abroad.

454
00:40:42,130 --> 00:40:44,265
You'll end up going before me.

455
00:40:45,612 --> 00:40:49,124
I met with Dr. Kim
and started treatment today.

456
00:40:50,302 --> 00:40:51,895
I'm going to try anything.

457
00:40:54,705 --> 00:40:56,423
So if we go together...

458
00:41:03,331 --> 00:41:05,425
When are you coming back?

459
00:41:06,006 --> 00:41:08,099
The idiots miss you a lot.

460
00:41:09,204 --> 00:41:10,922
I also...

461
00:41:21,672 --> 00:41:24,308
It'll be easier to add a heart emoji.

462
00:41:36,042 --> 00:41:39,709
[Seol Nae Il]

463
00:41:40,983 --> 00:41:45,780
Mini Min Hee, I can't go
because of the fried pork,

464
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:49,083
so I'll give you
my collection of chicken coupons later.

465
00:41:49,927 --> 00:41:51,562
Seol Nae Il.

466
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:55,161
If you hang up now,

467
00:41:56,273 --> 00:41:58,367
it's really over.

468
00:42:02,970 --> 00:42:06,375
You have a recommendation
for Salzburg Competition.

469
00:42:06,375 --> 00:42:08,227
All you need to do is to apply.

470
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:11,990
Come back quickly.
You have to send it back in two days.

471
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:14,024
It's the day of our performance.

472
00:42:16,727 --> 00:42:19,542
I won't ask you why you went to Jeju Island
without saying anything.

473
00:42:19,542 --> 00:42:20,709
Come back soon.

474
00:42:20,709 --> 00:42:22,450
I don't want to.

475
00:42:23,583 --> 00:42:27,876
Seol Nae Il, it's the opportunity
of a lifetime.

476
00:42:27,876 --> 00:42:28,918
I don't know what this is about.

477
00:42:28,918 --> 00:42:33,085
Once you leave,
I'll go back and take care of it.

478
00:42:34,368 --> 00:42:36,170
You know that I can't go study abroad.

479
00:42:37,808 --> 00:42:41,111
If you stay there,
I'm not coming back either.

480
00:42:44,485 --> 00:42:47,288
Tell me what this is all about
when you get here.

481
00:42:48,177 --> 00:42:50,855
I got sick of everything.

482
00:42:59,061 --> 00:43:00,863
Do you mean it?

483
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:05,042
If you tell me that you mean it,

484
00:43:05,042 --> 00:43:07,328
then I won't bother you again.

485
00:43:10,174 --> 00:43:18,158
Will you really give up
the piano, school and me?

486
00:43:33,572 --> 00:43:36,249
Yes, I mean it.

487
00:43:40,120 --> 00:43:42,047
Got it.

488
00:44:02,226 --> 00:44:03,903
Cha Yoo Jin.

489
00:44:08,119 --> 00:44:11,923
You took Min Hee's cellphone?
Why don't you give it back to her?

490
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:16,584
Hold on.

491
00:44:16,584 --> 00:44:19,500
Min Hee, let me check your cellphone.

492
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:21,417
[Seol Nae Il]

493
00:44:22,729 --> 00:44:24,072
Thanks.

494
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:31,000
Did you talk to Nae Il?

495
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:33,042
- When is she coming back?
- She's not.

496
00:44:33,042 --> 00:44:34,667
What do you mean?

497
00:44:34,667 --> 00:44:35,783
Did you have a fight?

498
00:44:35,783 --> 00:44:37,702
Even if you guys fight,
she should apply first.

499
00:44:37,702 --> 00:44:38,375
Let go.

500
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:41,918
You're not the only one
who worked hard for Nae Il's study abroad.

501
00:44:41,918 --> 00:44:44,383
I haven't given up on Nae Il's piano yet.

502
00:44:46,138 --> 00:44:47,459
If you don't go, I will.

503
00:44:47,459 --> 00:44:48,982
Do whatever you want.

504
00:45:38,569 --> 00:45:40,696
Isn't this too much for a carpool?

505
00:45:40,696 --> 00:45:44,125
This is not a carpool, it's a date.

506
00:45:44,125 --> 00:45:45,486
Wow!

507
00:45:49,958 --> 00:45:51,876
You brought a very nice car.

508
00:45:51,876 --> 00:45:54,804
It suits you, Maestro.

509
00:45:55,616 --> 00:45:57,500
Thank you for having me.

510
00:45:57,500 --> 00:45:59,837
Gas is very expensive these days.

511
00:46:02,578 --> 00:46:03,709
It's late.

512
00:46:03,709 --> 00:46:06,382
Let's hurry before we run late
for the students' performance.

513
00:46:07,643 --> 00:46:12,906
Not enough time,
yet enough for someone to bother us.

514
00:46:24,156 --> 00:46:28,125
Why do you have this?

515
00:46:28,125 --> 00:46:30,322
Baby gave it to me before she left.

516
00:46:31,889 --> 00:46:35,859
I just heard that Baby went to Jeju Island.

517
00:46:36,701 --> 00:46:40,042
She asked me to take you with me.

518
00:46:40,042 --> 00:46:42,251
I guess it must've been a big shock to her.

519
00:46:43,764 --> 00:46:48,042
Seol Nae Il told you to take me with you?

520
00:46:48,042 --> 00:46:51,834
She said you can go,
so she asked me to take you.

521
00:46:51,834 --> 00:46:53,429
What does that mean?

522
00:46:54,634 --> 00:46:57,353
Is there a secret
that only the two of you know?

523
00:47:02,157 --> 00:47:03,263
No.

524
00:47:04,626 --> 00:47:06,628
It doesn't matter now.

525
00:47:27,303 --> 00:47:29,209
Once the performance is over,
come out right away.

526
00:47:29,209 --> 00:47:31,216
I'll have a taxi ready for you.

527
00:47:31,932 --> 00:47:35,042
I heard Nae Il's house is close to the airport.

528
00:47:35,042 --> 00:47:37,473
If you go right after,
you'll be able to see her today.

529
00:47:38,460 --> 00:47:40,345
Don't be late.

530
00:47:45,824 --> 00:47:47,667
That watch.

531
00:47:47,667 --> 00:47:49,962
Isn't it the one
that Nae Il was carrying around?

532
00:47:52,332 --> 00:47:54,300
It's none of your business.

533
00:47:55,979 --> 00:48:00,029
I thought she might be interested in hypnosis
and found it odd.

534
00:48:00,029 --> 00:48:02,081
Now I see that it was yours.

535
00:48:10,839 --> 00:48:13,542
It's your first time going back
to the time on the plane,

536
00:48:13,542 --> 00:48:15,302
it's a surprise to me, too.

537
00:48:16,227 --> 00:48:19,459
Hypnotherapy is impossible
without the patient's awareness.

538
00:48:19,459 --> 00:48:20,459
It might work in a situation

539
00:48:20,459 --> 00:48:23,435
where you accept everything
without any resistance.

540
00:48:28,367 --> 00:48:34,381
When you open your eyes...

541
00:48:39,271 --> 00:48:41,823
you can get on a plane.

542
00:48:43,333 --> 00:48:45,834
You can get on a plane...

543
00:48:45,834 --> 00:48:50,963
and you can go anywhere.

544
00:48:53,788 --> 00:48:55,673
Seol Nae Il.

545
00:48:57,833 --> 00:49:00,928
Does she think she cured me with hypnosis?

546
00:49:01,589 --> 00:49:03,891
Is that why she's telling me to go abroad?

547
00:49:06,989 --> 00:49:10,000
That is just like you, Seol Nae Il.

548
00:49:27,423 --> 00:49:29,000
Why isn't he coming out?

549
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,584
Right?

550
00:49:30,584 --> 00:49:33,751
Why isn't Yoo Jin coming out?

551
00:49:33,751 --> 00:49:37,926
I'm not sure. He's usually not late.

552
00:50:32,991 --> 00:50:35,126
I'm shaking.

553
00:50:42,942 --> 00:50:46,078
They'll do well. Don't worry.

554
00:51:07,693 --> 00:51:11,038
Tchaikovsky's Violin Concerto in D major.

555
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:15,584
This is Tchaikovsky's only violin concerto.

556
00:51:15,584 --> 00:51:19,979
It was criticized harshly as terrible music
at its premiere performance.

557
00:51:19,979 --> 00:51:24,116
But in the end, it was acknowledged
for its beauty and true value.

558
00:51:25,356 --> 00:51:28,951
Just like my friends who used to be 'losers'.

559
00:51:51,817 --> 00:51:53,542
Yoo Il Lak.

560
00:51:53,542 --> 00:51:58,275
To me, there is no other soloist
who is better than you in the orchestra.

561
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:25,542
It's not my orchestra.

562
00:52:25,542 --> 00:52:29,056
We're in this orchestra together.

563
00:52:33,150 --> 00:52:34,500
Will you be really okay?

564
00:52:34,500 --> 00:52:36,417
Yes, I'm okay with it.

565
00:52:36,417 --> 00:52:38,792
What if we lose?

566
00:52:38,792 --> 00:52:42,417
Even if we end up losing,
we won't have any regrets.

567
00:52:42,417 --> 00:52:46,281
Let's show them how hard we worked.

568
00:52:51,448 --> 00:52:53,083
Almighty Cha, it's okay.

569
00:52:53,083 --> 00:52:54,709
Just do what we did at the rehearsal.

570
00:52:54,709 --> 00:52:56,458
It's okay, Cha Yoo Jin.

571
00:52:57,174 --> 00:53:00,334
Of course.
I'm confident about my instruments.

572
00:53:00,334 --> 00:53:03,340
You mean, the orchestra is
the conductor's instrument?

573
00:53:07,646 --> 00:53:09,782
Rising Star!

574
00:54:20,427 --> 00:54:21,937
Bravo!

575
00:54:40,614 --> 00:54:45,459
Finally, they found Han Eum's own sound.

576
00:54:45,459 --> 00:54:49,399
Yes, they sure did.

577
00:55:25,868 --> 00:55:29,672
Now, my job is done.

578
00:55:38,088 --> 00:55:40,057
I'm so proud of you, my boyfriend!

579
00:55:42,319 --> 00:55:44,618
I didn't get nervous or get anything wrong?

580
00:55:44,618 --> 00:55:47,037
No, you didn't get nervous
or get anything wrong.

581
00:55:47,037 --> 00:55:48,834
You were totally awesome.

582
00:55:48,834 --> 00:55:51,083
I liked you because you were cute,

583
00:55:51,083 --> 00:55:53,919
but now I see that you're awesome too.

584
00:55:53,919 --> 00:55:57,667
If you fall for me more,
how will you go to Vienna?

585
00:55:57,667 --> 00:56:00,725
I know. How could I leave?

586
00:56:07,766 --> 00:56:11,236
Goodness. They're shooting a movie.

587
00:56:12,479 --> 00:56:14,709
Thank God we don't have
to deal with that for long.

588
00:56:14,709 --> 00:56:16,375
I can't stand it anymore.

589
00:56:16,375 --> 00:56:19,167
But they look happy.

590
00:56:19,167 --> 00:56:21,079
I want to date someone, too.

591
00:56:22,629 --> 00:56:25,450
Yeah, they deserve each other.

592
00:56:25,450 --> 00:56:26,918
Chills!

593
00:56:29,223 --> 00:56:30,690
Mini Min Hee!

594
00:56:51,033 --> 00:56:53,334
Check the time and the gate.

595
00:56:53,334 --> 00:56:55,947
If we don't hit traffic,
we'll be there on time.

596
00:57:12,140 --> 00:57:13,398
Traffic again.

597
00:57:14,375 --> 00:57:16,459
It'll also take time to find Nae Il.

598
00:57:16,459 --> 00:57:18,304
If there's anymore delay...

599
00:57:21,631 --> 00:57:23,224
What's wrong?

600
00:57:24,069 --> 00:57:25,328
It's nothing.

601
00:57:26,918 --> 00:57:29,000
[Boarding Pass]
[Gimpo to Jeju]

602
00:57:47,217 --> 00:57:49,561
What's wrong? We have no time for this.

603
00:57:56,602 --> 00:57:58,445
I can't get on.

604
00:58:00,670 --> 00:58:02,292
We don't have time.

605
00:58:02,292 --> 00:58:04,167
Wait.

606
00:58:04,167 --> 00:58:06,612
I'm not feeling well. Hold on.

607
00:58:09,721 --> 00:58:13,149
Then you just watch. I'll bring Nae Il back.

608
00:58:16,618 --> 00:58:18,375
You're hesitating
after coming all the way here?

609
00:58:18,375 --> 00:58:20,073
Give it to me.

610
00:58:21,066 --> 00:58:22,667
Stop messing around.

611
00:58:22,667 --> 00:58:24,452
Stop playing and give it back to me.

612
00:58:30,640 --> 00:58:34,151
Go. I don't want to see you off.

613
00:59:12,970 --> 00:59:15,606
Honey, wake up! Honey!

614
00:59:21,204 --> 00:59:22,042
Honey!

615
00:59:22,042 --> 00:59:24,345
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

616
01:00:11,107 --> 01:00:14,334
Mini Min Hee, did the performance go well?

617
01:00:14,334 --> 01:00:17,190
Of course. We did well against Sae Hyun.

618
01:00:19,497 --> 01:00:22,479
What about Sunbae?

619
01:00:22,479 --> 01:00:26,751
I don't know.
He went somewhere after the performance.

620
01:00:26,751 --> 01:00:29,202
We can't even bring up your name these days.

621
01:00:30,881 --> 01:00:32,557
I see.

622
01:00:37,513 --> 01:00:39,931
About your competition...

623
01:00:40,762 --> 01:00:43,143
Okay, you do what you want to do.

624
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,083
If I entered the competition
and won the first place,

625
01:00:47,083 --> 01:00:50,056
I thought I'd be able
to go study abroad with Yoo Jin.

626
01:00:51,026 --> 01:00:54,621
But I regret it a little right now.

627
01:00:55,364 --> 01:00:58,500
I should've said goodbye to Sunbae in Seoul.

628
01:00:59,364 --> 01:01:04,500
If Sunbae sees Professor Viera,
I could've listened to the story.

629
01:01:04,500 --> 01:01:08,783
I could work really hard
and go study abroad, too.

630
01:01:09,749 --> 01:01:12,626
Then Sunbae will be a great conductor,

631
01:01:12,626 --> 01:01:14,584
I'll be a pianist

632
01:01:14,584 --> 01:01:17,750
and our orchestra will be Rising Star.

633
01:01:18,383 --> 01:01:20,302
Mini Min Hee,

634
01:01:20,302 --> 01:01:24,048
just thinking about it
makes me really happy...

635
01:01:41,535 --> 01:01:45,506
I came to bring you back, Nae Il.
